The paper deals with caching in wireless networks, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The optimization aspect of the paper falls under the category of systems and control (SY). The use of stochastic geometry and gamma approximation techniques suggests a possible fit with multimedia (MM) and data structures (DS) categories.
